<div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on"><div style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">After the grand release of <a href="http://www.mozilla.com/en-US/firefox/fx/">Firefox 4 for desktop</a> last week, now Mozilla releases Firefox 4 for Android and Maemo devices. Go grab it from the <a href="https://market.android.com/details?id=org.mozilla.firefox">android market</a> or scan from the <a href="https://spark.mozilla.org/media/img/qrcode.png">QR code</a> or download directly from <a href="http://www.mozilla.com/en-US/m/">Firefox Mobile</a>. It is offered in more than 12 languages.</span></div><div style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif;"><br /></div><span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif; font-size: small;"> </span><div style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">Firefox 4 for mobile has one of the coolest feature like <strong>Sync</strong>,  where you can sync your preferences, open tabs, history, bookmarks,  passwords across mobile and desktop and the data is encrypted via a 26  character key. Other features include tabbed browsing, password manager.</span></div><div style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif;"><br /></div><span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif; font-size: small;"> </span><div style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">You can share a page directly with a single click to facebook, Email,  Twitter or save it as a PDF for offline use. Customize your browser and  make it as you like using the <a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/mobile/?browse=featured">Add-ons</a>. Go play with it now!</span></div><span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif; font-size: small;"> </span><div style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">In addition to the above features, Firefox mobile also supports<strong> CSS3</strong> and<strong> HTML 5</strong> ( can watch Youtube without flash installed ).</span></div><div style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif;"><br /></div><span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif; font-size: small;"> </span><div style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">A website is specially launched to celebrate Firefox going Mobile, <a href="https://spark.mozilla.org/">Spark</a>,  a game that challenges you to share with friends to help the flame of  the open Web glow bright. Now, go and start the spark! It is just like  the <a href="http://glow.mozilla.org/">Glow</a> website which was created for the release of Desktop version.</span></div><div style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif;"><br /></div><span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif; font-size: small;"> </span><div style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://blog.mozilla.com/blog/2011/03/29/mozilla-launches-firefox-4-for-android-allowing-users-to-take-the-power-and-customization-of-firefox-everywhere-2/">Firefox</a> also noted that it is three times faster than the stock browser on Android. Check out the latest <a href="https://demos.mozilla.org/">Web O' Wonder </a>demos, you can even create one.</span></div><div style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif;"><br /></div><span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif; font-size: small;"> </span><div style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong><em>Overall Firefox 4 for Mobile is just Awesome! :)</em></strong> </span></div></div>
